PROFESSIONAL PROPOSAL FOR LMS DEVELOPMENT
Client: School of Mathematics Nigeria
Prepared by: Edudje Wisdom (Uplix)
Date: 28/09/2025
1. PROJECT OVERVIEW
School of Mathematics Nigeria plans to build a modern, accessible, and scalable Learning 
Management System (LMS) tailored specifically for mathematics education.
The objective is to create an affordable platform that delivers both free and premium courses, 
enhances student engagement, and simplifies course administration for instructors.
The LMS will run seamlessly on mobile and desktop, supporting thousands of users without 
requiring expensive hosting.
2. CORE FEATURES
 Student Dashboard
A simplified, intuitive dashboard containing:
Personalized welcome message
Sidebar/top navigation
List of enrolled courses
Quick-access sections:
Free Courses
Premium Courses
Profile Settings
Learning Progress
Support & Help
 Course Management System (CMS)
Admin-only tools to manage all content:
Add, edit, delete courses
Upload learning materials:
Video content via YouTube/Vimeo/Google drive embeds (cost-saving)
PDF notes and documents
Quizzes (MCQ & short-answer)
Categorize courses by levels:
JAMB
WAEC
SS1
SS2
Others
 Payment Integration
Integrated with Paystack or Flutterwave for secure payments:
One-time purchases
Subscriptions (Monthly / Quarterly)
Automatic unlocking of premium content
Email confirmation after successful payment
 Learning Progress Tracking
Completion status for all courses
Quiz scores & attempts
Progress bars and visual indicators for motivation
 Admin Panel
A complete control center for administrators:
Course & content management
Student accounts management
Payment history monitoring
Basic analytics (enrollment, revenue, engagement)
 Mobile-Responsive, Fast UI
Fully optimized for mobile phones
TailwindCSS-based modern interface
Lightweight for low-data usage
 Support & Notifications
In-app contact form
WhatsApp support button
Optional email alerts for:
New course uploads
Payment confirmations
Progress reminders
3. TECH STACK
Layer Technology
Frontend next.js + TailwindCSS
Backend  Supabase
Authentication Firebase Auth or Supabase Auth
Payments Paystack / Flutterwave
Content Delivery YouTube, Vimeo, PDFs, Google drive 
All technologies chosen for scalability, low cost, and ease of maintenance.
4. PROJECT TIMELINE
Task Duration
UI/UX Design 5days
Frontend Development 7 days
Backend Integration 10days
Payment Integration 4 days
Testing & Optimization 3 days
Total Duration 29-30 working days
5. BUDGET BREAKDOWN
Item Cost (₦)
Full LMS Development ₦250,000
Payment Integration Included
Admin Panel Included
Basic SEO & Launch Included
Domain & Hosting Setup ₦10,000 (optional)
Post-Launch Support ₦15,000/month (optional)
Payment Plan
60% upfront – ₦150,000
40% on final delivery – ₦100,000
6. DELIVERABLES
The client will receive:
A fully responsive, modern LMS
Student dashboard with live content
Admin dashboard with management tools
Integrated payment system
Complete deployment on a domain
Training session for staff/admin
Optional ongoing maintenance
7. FUTURE UPGRADE OPTIONS (Not included in current cost)
Certificate generation system
Full mobile app (Android/iOS using React Native)
Community forums or student messaging
Advanced analytics dashboard for engagement and revenue tracking
8. CONCLUSION
This proposed LMS will help School of Mathematics Nigeria transition into a digital-first learning 
institution. It is cost-effective, scalable, easy to use, and built for long-term growth.
With this platform, the school can deliver structured mathematics education nationwide while 
